[0.000, "o", "  - Repo paths resolved to ~/.claude/project-repos.env + .json\r\n\r\n=== Customising repo paths ===\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  Repos are auto-discovered in $HOME, $HOME/code, $HOME/projects, etc.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    export PROJECT_REPOS_DIR=/path/to/your/repos && ./install.sh\r\n    ./install.sh --search-dir /custom/path\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "    ./install.sh --deep-scan     # scan git remotes (slower)\r\n  Per-repo overrides go in ~/.claude/project-repos.local.env, e.g.:\r\n    PROJECT_REPO_API=/custom/path/to/api-repo\r\n\r\n=== Next steps ===\r\n  1. Edit repos.conf to list your actual projects, then re-run ./install.sh\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "  2. Edit projects/*.md to describe each project's stack and conventions\r\n  3. (Optional) Configure MCP servers (see docs/MCP-SETUP.md)\r\n  4. Start Claude Code from this directory:  claude\r\n\r\n"]
